'''Polygamy''' was the act of having more than one spouse at a time. Because of the low male birthrate among [[Cerean/Legends|Cereans]], polygamy was a generally accepted [[Marriage/Legends|practice]] on [[Cerea/Legends|Cerea]]. While the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order's]] [[Jedi Code/Legends|tenets]] forbade any emotional attachment, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Ki-Adi-Mundi/Legends|Ki-Adi-Mundi]] was allowed to take [[Mundi family|multiple wives]]. He had four wives, two of which were known as [[Shea]] and [[Mawin]].

==Behind the scenes==
Polygamy was referenced in ''[[Labyrinth of Evil]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Prelude to Rebellion]]''. It was first [[canon]]ically identified as "polygamy" in ''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''.

